---
description: Instructions for when to use JSDoc
globs: ["**/*.ts", "**/*.d.ts", "**/*.js"]
---

Always use JSDoc when you can
Annotate everything possible
Annotate the top of the file (with @module if it is one and the description), interface, function
The only variables I want you to annotate though are the top-level constants (const)
The only thing I don't want you to with JSDoc is to include the types in the annotation (that is what the TS is for)

Bad:

```ts
// Configuration interface for each target
export interface CopyTarget {
	src: string;          // Absolute path to the source directory
	serveAt?: string;     // Optional: URL prefix for dev server (e.g., "/aero/sandbox")
}
```

Good
```ts
/** Configuration interface for each target */
export interface CopyTarget {
  /** Absolute path to the source directory */
	src: string;
  /** URL prefix for dev server (e.g., `/aero/sandbox`) */
	serveAt?: string;
}
```

> Also notice: you don't need to put `Optional:` as the types imply that and you use backticks when quoting something in JSDoc/MD